            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ginger paste</strong>, <strong>remaining garam masala</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> and the <strong>baked beans </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min further or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1665138125864-x200.jpg",
